{"questionId":"2681272","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a storm, the total volume, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math> , of rainwater that enters the gutter can be modelled by a function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time, in seconds, since the start of the storm.</p>\n<p>It was determined that the <strong>rate</strong> at which rainwater entered the gutter could be modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>3000</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>During any <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math>-second period, if the volume of rainwater entering the gutter is greater than the volume of the gutter, it will overflow.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></math>, correct to three significant figures.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>arc</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>length</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>arc length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>cm</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></math> correct to 3 significant figures&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2681272","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that θ=2.08, correct to three significant figures.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
